div.p:
               TO Vindicate, and deliver my ſelf, from the imputation of Sarcaſtick, bitter, too looſe, & liberall ſpeaches, agaynſt the moſt Noble, Worthie, and Tranſcendant Sexe of WOMEN, (which ſome, knowing their own imperfect weakneſſe, may apprehend to be
Calumnies, and detractiue to the whole Sexe) I here make humble Oblation;

 &, with all Reverence, preſent vnto your Ladiſhips Honorable Hands, this litle TREATISE; as a part of my Studie, in my weariſome Journie, this halfe yeare bypaſt, in forraygne Countreys.
